It also has no such ID card of about five million new voters in 2012.
In addition, getting a required ID card often costs more than a hundred dollars.
The new restrictions disproportionately affect young people, minority members and low-income people.
25% of African Americans, 15% of those with income below $35,000; 18% of citizens over 65 and 20% of voters aged 18 to 29, therefore, do not have the required photo ID.
